snippet.title: Simple History
snippet.description:
Welcome to the Official Simple History Channel. Simple History visualizes the past, bringing history to life through animation. 

Witness how people lived throughout history: their culture, developments in technology, epic battles and events.

Explore what it was like to be in the trenches of the First World War, a plundering pirate in the Caribbean or a factory worker in the Industrial Revolution! 

Have a business proposition such as a sponsorship proposal? get in touch by email below!

Fan mail / art: simplehistorycommunity@gmail.com

Simple History started in September 2013 with its first book title 'Simple History: WWI'. 

Some titles include:
Simple History: World War I
Simple History: World War II
Simple History: The American Revolution
Simple History: The Vietnam War
Simple History: The Cold War
Simple History: The Russian Revolution
Simple History: the American Civil war
Copyright: DO NOT reupload our content on Youtube or other social media without expressed permission.

snippet.title: Extra Credits
snippet.description:
P3YKN3
More info about our shows is available at: http://becausegamesmatter.com

Join us on Extra Credits every Wednesday as we take a deeper look at games: how they are made, what they mean, and how we can make them better. 

Join us on Extra History every Saturday to explore little-known but dramatic adventures in world history! 

Join us on Extra Sci Fi every Tuesday as we take an analytical look at the greatest works of science fiction.

Join us on Extra Mythology every (other) Monday as we delve into some of the coolest stories from world mythology you may never have heard of!

snippet.title: History Seekers
snippet.description: Join History Seekers' hosts Heath Jones and Scott Duncan as they explore a myriad of topics related to the recovery and preservation of history. Adventures await in metal detecting, bottle digging, Indian artifacts, fossils, meteorites, and much more!

snippet.title: The Great War
snippet.description:
The Great War covers the First World War from 1914 to 1923 – in real time. Every other week, Jesse Alexander cover the important events that influenced the world 100 years ago. Form 2014 - 2018, Indiana Neidell followed the main events of what is classically considered as World War 1 on a weekly basis. 

You can support our show on Patreon: http://patreon.com/thegreatwar

snippet.title: History Class
snippet.description:
I was a history teacher for a short time. I was disappointed because most of my students were not interested in learning history. The I understand that there are only a few people around the world who are passionate about history.

From that point I decided to make history videos in English (although I am not a native speaker of English), only for those who are interested in learning new things related to history. Here I will upload all kind of history videos, about main events, explained so everybody can understand what happened.

snippet.title: Ancient History Lover
snippet.description:
This channel is educational 
if you love history and you enjoy learning about World History then this channel is for you.

"History... is, indeed, little more than the register of the 'crimes, follies, and misfortunes' of mankind. But what experience and history teach is this - that peoples and governments have never learned anything from history, or acted on principles deduced from it. "
Georg Wilhelm Friedrich Hegel








For new subscribers i highly recommend that they start watching videos from Channel's playlist
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n_rXvze-RTU&list=PL594AstrUMtjXJRyiQAPkQjsXq4WBqjbK

If you want to contact me, you can send me an Email on Ancient.history.yt@gmail.com

And also i like to mention that my channel is non-monetized channel. so if you see an ad on one of my videos that probably belongs to owner of the video.

snippet.title: American Museum of Natural History
snippet.description: The American Museum of Natural History is one of the world's preeminent scientific and cultural institutions. Since its founding in 1869, the Museum has advanced its global mission to discover, interpret and disseminate information about human cultures, the natural world and the universe through a wide-ranging program of scientific research, education and exhibition. The Museum is renowned for its exhibitions and scientific collections, which serve as a field guide to the entire planet and present a panorama of the world's cultures.
